It’s been 10 years since Arjun Kapoor (@arjunkapoor), a truly genial actor made his debut in Habib Faisal’s Ishaqzaade. His Parma Chauhan was a heady mix of cute and macho, and the actor played it to perfection. After the crackling debut, he further explored and proved his range as a true-blue commercial hero with, Aurangzeb and Gunday. It would be reductive to call our cover star for June, Dulquer Salmaan (@dqsalmaan) a mere celebrity. He is ostensibly a national sensation. From debuting in Second Show — a movie with a bunch of newcomers that no one knew about — to grabbing his first Filmfare award for Best Actor (2012), to then, delivering a bonafide performance in Bangalore Days (2014) — which became one of the highest-grossing Malayalam films of all time — it has taken Dulquer a decade to firmly established himself as an actor in his own right and with immense credibility, in an industry where his father and Malayalam superstar, Mammootty’s shadow still looms large. Through it all, Dulquer has won many hearts, be it as Yaazhan from Hey Sinamika (2021) or as Aadhi from O Kadhal Kanmani (2015). In our cover story this month, Dulquer spills the tea on his upcoming projects and his evolution over the course of the last 10 years. Coming soon ✨

During the Boxing Day Test at the MCG, Virat Kohli collided shoulders with Australian debutant Sam Konstas while crossing paths on the pitch, sparking a heated exchange. The altercation required intervention from umpires and players, with the ICC later fining Kohli 20% of his match fee and adding one demerit point to his record. Despite criticism from former cricketers like Michael Vaughan and Ricky Ponting, Kohli avoided suspension due to a clean disciplinary record.

Meanwhile, 19-year-old Konstas impressed with a rapid 60 off 65 balls, showcasing his resilience amid the drama. Downplaying the clash, he stated, “Emotions got to both of us.” The incident underlined the intensity of the series and introduced Konstas as a promising talent in Australian cricket. For Kohli, the episode served as a reminder of the scrutiny faced by seasoned players.

Do you think the fine was fair?
